SECTION 3. TACIR may request information and input from state and local
governmental entities, industry stakeholders, academic experts, and advocacy organizations, as
necessary to conduct the study. State and local governmental entities shall, to the extent
permitted by law, provide information requested by TACIR. TACIR shall conduct the study
using TACIR's existing resources.
SECTION 4. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
